# Isolated Machine (Limited Access)
#
# This machine owns one domain repo and reads the shared identity
# layer. It does NOT have access to other domain repos (e.g., work
# data stays off this machine). Customize for your setup.

## Shared Memory

This machine has access to the following memory repos:
- **homelab-memory**: ~/repos/homelab-memory/ (read-write, source of truth)
- **shared-identity**: ~/repos/shared-identity/ (read-write)

### Rules
- On session start, pull shared-identity before reading
- Domain-specific memories → homelab-memory
- Universal memories or personal project notes → shared-identity
- After writing to a shared repo:
  ```bash
  cd ~/repos/<repo> && git add -A && git commit -m "[homelab] description" && git push
  ```
- This machine has NO access to work-memory. Do not reference or attempt to read work-specific context.
